    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="840"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/287.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of 11th instant. Investigation shows an increase of duties
                    collected and larger importations. Treasury report for fiscal year ending
                    September 30, 1911, shows receipts from all sources $478,000; disbursements,
                    $490,000. Floating debt since the finding of the Debt Commission, $201,000.
                    These are the latest authentic figures available. The disquieting rumor was
                    caused by those who would reap large profits from danger to or failure of the
                    loan. The General Receiver’s presence would stop further misrepresentation, and
                    he is anxiously expected by the Government, which has absolute confidence in its
                    ability to meet the requirements of the new loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crum.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
